# Example environment configuration for Security Arena
# This file is safe to commit; it contains ONLY placeholders.
# Copy to ".env" at the repo root and edit (see scenarios/security_arena/bulk_scenarios/README.md).

# =============================================================================
# Profile A — Cloud OpenAI (default for competition / CI)
# =============================================================================
OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-api-key-here
OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# ARENA_OLLAMA_MODEL is ignored when using cloud unless you use the bulk runner’s --model / env to rewrite TOMLs.

# =============================================================================
# Profile B — Local Ollama (swap in place of Profile A for Mac / offline runs)
# Ollama exposes an OpenAI-compatible HTTP API; agents use the same client code.
# =============================================================================
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=ollama
# ARENA_OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2:3b
#
# Pick a pulled model: `ollama list`. For ~3B–8B on 16 GB RAM, common picks are llama3.2:3b,
# mistral, llama3, or qwen2.5:3b — avoid huge models unless you know they fit.
# Per-run override: `uv run python .../run_bulk_scenarios.py --model your/tag`
